{"meta": {"centerNodeId": "taxonomy-species-neopelma-chrysolophum", "centerNodeType": "taxonomy", "generatedAt": "2026-05-28T16:28:22", "includedNodeCount": 3, "includedLinkCount": 2, "layoutMode": "precomputed-static"}, "center": {"id": "taxonomy-species-neopelma-chrysolophum", "name": "Serra do Mar tyrant-manakin", "type": "taxonomy"}, "nodes": [{"id": "bird-serra-do-mar-tyrant-manakin-23d56d9c", "name": "Serra do Mar tyrant-manakin", "englishName": "Serra do Mar tyrant-manakin", "latinName": "Neopelma chrysolophum", "type": "bird", "status": "LC", "summary": "The Serra do Mar tyrant-manakin (Neopelma chrysolophum), also known as the Serra do Mar neopelma and Serra tyrant-manakin, is a species of bird in the family Pipridae, the manakins. It is endemic to Brazil. Taxonomy and systematics The Serra do Mar tyrant-manakin was originally described in 1944 as a subspecies of Wied's tyrant-manakin (Neopelma aurifrons). They were separated based on a study published in 1995. The Serra do Mar tyrant-manakin's further taxonomy is unsettled. Worldwide taxonomic systems assign it to genus Neopelma. However, the independent South American Classification Committee follows the recommendation of a paper published in 2023 and assigns it to its own genus, Protopelma. The Serra do Mar tyrant-manakin is monotypic. Description The Serra do Mar tyrant-manakin is 13 to 13.5 cm (5.1 to 5.3 in) long and weighs 13.5 to 14.9 g (0.48 to 0.53 oz). The sexes have the same plumage. Adults have a conspicuous yellow patch in the middle of the crown. The rest of their face, their upperparts, wings, and tail are olive-green. Their throat is dull grayish white, their upper breast grayish olive, and their lower breast and belly pale sulphur-yellow. They have a pale grayish mauve iris, a grayish bill, and grayish legs and feet. Distribution and habitat The Serra do Mar tyrant-manakin is found in coastal southeastern Brazil from east-central Minas Gerais and Rio de Janeiro state south at least to far southern São Paulo state and possibly beyond into Paraná. It inhabits the Serra do Mar coastal forests, where it greatly favors the forest edge, dense secondary forest, and areas of stunted woody vegetation. It shuns the forest interior. In elevation it ranges between 1,150 and 1,800 m (3,800 and 5,900 ft). Behavior Movement The Serra do Mar tyrant-manakin is believed to be a year-round resident. Feeding The Serra do Mar tyrant-manakin feeds mostly on small fruits and also includes insects in its diet. It plucks or grabs its food from vegetation with a short sally from a perch; sometimes it briefly hovers. Breeding Serra do Mar tyrant-manakin males sing from a horizontal perch. Nothing else is known about the species' breeding biology. Vocalization The Serra do Mar tyrant-manakin's song is a \"series of random, well-separated notes, such as a slow, staccato rih-tjew-tjew-tjuh, rrítju (rr stressed), tjuwtju, or vrrrrrú\". Status The IUCN has assessed the Serra do Mar tyrant-manakin as being of Least Concern. It has a limited range; its population size is not known and is believed to be decreasing. No immediate threats have been identified. It is considered common. \"Much suitable habitat persists in protected areas within its rather limited range.\" References External links Graphic and Article", "shortSummary": "The Serra do Mar tyrant-manakin (Neopelma chrysolophum), also known as the Serra do Mar neopelma and Serra tyrant-manakin, is a species of…", "locations": ["米纳斯吉拉斯州", "里約熱內盧州", "圣保罗州", "巴拉那州", "Serra do Mar coastal forests", "次生林"], "lat": -19.78222222, "lng": -43.95138889, "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/0f/Neopelma_chrysolophum.jpeg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-neopelma", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-neopelma-chrysolophum", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-neopelma", "species": "taxonomy-species-neopelma-chrysolophum"}, "expandable": true, "x": -544.15, "y": -327.57, "z": 77.17}, {"id": "taxonomy-genus-neopelma", "name": "Neopelma", "latinName": "Neopelma", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "genus", "summary": "Neopelma（Neopelma）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联5种鸟类，如Pale-bellied tyrant-manakin、Saffron-crested tyrant-manakin、Wied's tyrant-manakin等5种鸟类。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 5, "x": -207.31, "y": 502.47, "z": 19.29}, {"id": "taxonomy-species-neopelma-chrysolophum", "name": "Serra do Mar tyrant-manakin", "latinName": "Neopelma chrysolophum", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "species", "summary": "Serra do Mar tyrant-manakin（Neopelma chrysolophum）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联1种鸟类，如Serra do Mar tyrant-manakin。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 1, "x": -544.15, "y": -327.57, "z": 87.62}], "links": [{"key": "bird-serra-do-mar-tyrant-manakin-23d56d9c__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-neopelma-chrysolophum", "source": "bird-serra-do-mar-tyrant-manakin-23d56d9c", "target": "taxonomy-species-neopelma-chrysolophum", "relation": "belongs_to_species", "label": "属于种", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 中的种字段补充。"}, {"key": "taxonomy-species-neopelma-chrysolophum__belongs_to_genus__taxonomy-genus-neopelma", "source": "taxonomy-species-neopelma-chrysolophum", "target": "taxonomy-genus-neopelma", "relation": "belongs_to_genus", "label": "属于属", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 分类字段补充：Serra do Mar tyrant-manakin 属于属 Neopelma。"}]}
